The purpose of a hash function is to distribute the elements across different buckets and minimize collisions. A good hash function should map each element to a unique bucket as much as possible, while also producing a relatively balanced distribution of elements across all buckets. 

To improve the `hashcode` function for strings, a common approach is to use a combination of the characters in the string to generate a hash value. For example, the following implementation uses the ASCII codes of each character in the string to create a hash value:

```
int hashcode(const string& str) {
    int hash = 0;
    for (char c : str) {
        hash = hash * 31 + static_cast<int>(c);
    }
    return hash;
}
```

This implementation creates a unique hash value for each string based on the combination of its characters, reducing the likelihood of collisions and improving hashing performance.

